<item>
            <title>[CXF-6092] When there is bad connection/timeout, ClientImpl throws NullPointerException</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-6092</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When the connection when executing WebService all is interrupted or timed out, there is some kind of racing issue and the result is&lt;br/&gt;
(the stacktrace and src code is from v. 2.7.11, but the same code is also in the other versions)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Caused by: java.lang.NullPointerException&lt;br/&gt;
    at org.apache.cxf.endpoint.ClientImpl.invoke(ClientImpl.java:396)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I suppose the problem is that when the connection is timed out/closed, the &lt;br/&gt;
destroy() method is called in ClientImpl, where there is a statement that sets &lt;br/&gt;
responseContext = null;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;and then in the finalize block of the invoke, there is the code that produces the NPE:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;} finally {&lt;br/&gt;
            if (context != null) {&lt;br/&gt;
                Map&amp;lt;String, Object&amp;gt; resp = CastUtils.cast((Map&amp;lt;?, ?&amp;gt;)context.get(RESPONSE_CONTEXT));&lt;br/&gt;
                if (resp != null) &lt;/p&gt;
{
--NPE-----&amp;gt;                    responseContext.put(Thread.currentThread(), resp);
                }
&lt;p&gt;            }&lt;br/&gt;
        }&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;One possible solutions is to add verification also for not null value in responseContext.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
